onal name <i>Elisse</i> (earlier <i>Elisedd</i>, a derivative of <i>elus</i> ‘kindly, benevolent’). As usual in Welsh, the stress in <i>Elisse</i> is on the penultimate syllable <i>-li-</i>, which shifts to initial <i>El-</i> when the name is shortened to <i>Elis</i>. It later became confused with <i>Ellis</i> in 1 above."]},{"name":"Iley","meanings":["English (Durham): habitational name from Brent Eleigh or Monks Eleigh in Suffolk, or perhaps from Illey in Worcestershire. The Suffolk placename derives from an Old English personal name <i>Illa</i> (genitive <i>Illan</i>) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The Worcestershire placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Hilla</i> or <i>Illa</i> + <i>lēah</i>. Alternatively, the name may be a variant of   Ely  .","Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Ihle  ."]},{"name":"Elley","meanings":["English: variant of   Ely   or   Ella  ."]},{"name":"Ealy","meanings":["English: variant of   Ely  ."]},{"name":"Eley","meanings":["English: variant of   Ely  .","German: from a vernacular form of the medieval personal name <i>Eligius</i> (see   Eligio  ), a Christian saint's name."]},{"name":"Ealey","meanings":["English: variant of   Ely  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Ely was born about 1517, in Tenterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She married William Elye about 1539, in Tenterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1517–":"umbes 1517–Surnud","1517–Male":"1517–Surnud","1545–1615":"1545–1615","1517–Female":"1517–Surnud","1545":"1545","Abt 1517":"umbes 1517","Abt 1539":"umbes 1539","1517":"1517","1615":"1615","of Tenterden, Kent, England":"Tenterden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tenterden, Kent, England":"Tenterden, Kent, Inglisma